sentence:
• salesforce.com, inc's ( CRM ) shares increased 3.4% after announcing fiscal third quarter revenues of $2.145 billion, beating the Zacks Consensus Estimate of $2.116 billion
• Shares of The Gap, Inc. ( GPS ) slumped 16.6% after reporting fiscal third quarter net sales of $3,798 million, falling 1.6% from the year-ago figure
• Ross Stores Inc. ( ROST ) shares advanced 3.8% after disclosing fiscal third-quarter earnings of $0.62 per share, outpacing the Zacks Consensus Estimate of $0.56
• Shares of Intuit Inc. ( INTU ) rose 1.9% after posting fiscal first quarter adjusted loss of $0.11 per share, narrower than the Zacks Consensus Estimate of a loss of $0.17 per share
